scene_description: the background is made of cyan pixels. there are three rectangles near the base of the grid. from top to bottom they are made of blue pixels, red pixels, and green pixels. each rectangle has a right and left side that is a different color. from top to bottom the borders of the rectangles are green, blue, and yellow. there are three shapes near the top of the grid that are composed of various colors.
literal_instruction: to begin, replace all of the pixels that are not cyan that are placed above the 16th row from the bottom with cyan pixels. next, place yellow pixels in the green rectangle. in the 2nd row from the bottom, place yellow pixels in the following columns from the right: 6th, 7th, 8th, 9th, 10th, 14th, and 15th. then, in the 3rd row from the bottom, place yellow pixels in the 14th and 15th columns from the left. next, place blue pixels in the red rectangle. in the 7th row from the bottom, place blue pixels in the following columns from the right: 5th, 6th, 7th, 8th, 9th, 10th, 11th, 19th, 20th, 21th. then, in the 8th row from the bottom, place blue pixels in the following columns from the right: 4th, 5th, 11th, 12th. next, in the 9th row from the bottom, place blue pixels in the following columns from the right: 5th, 6th, 7th, 8th, 9th, 10th, 11th. now, place green pixels in the blue rectangle. in the 12th row from the bottom, place green pixels in the following columns from the left: 3rd, 4th, 5th, 6th, 7th. next, in the 13th row from the bottom, place green pixels in the following columns from the left: 3rd, 7th. finally, in the 14th row from the bottom, place green pixels in the following columns from the left: 3rd, 4th, 5th, 6th, 7th. all done!
